==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poonga oil
<hw>Poon"ga oil`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of oil used in India for
lamps, and for boiling with dammar for pitching vessels. It is pressed
from the seeds of a leguminous tree (<spn>Pongamia
glabra</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poop</ent>⟦br⟧
